End-to-End Marketing on Your 
Data Cloud with AI

Let's talk a bit more about this hot subject around AI agents and agentic 
capabilities. From your perspective, what's real and what is hype?

For marketers facing all this change, all this opportunity, all this 
challenge for 2025, what parting advice would you give them?

Why the Next Wave Beyond 
CDPs is AI Decisioning

Can you start by telling us a little about Hightouch and your background 
before founding the company?

The phrase Composable CDP definitely caught on. Overall, composability 
has become a rallying cry — if not a buzzword — in the martech industry. 
What makes a product truly composable?

Can you share a few real-world use cases or examples of such AI 
Decisioning in practice?

What kind of AI is this? Are we talking about classic AI, machine learning, 
or is this generative AI?

If you go back to today's state of AI Decisioning, if you want to implement 
it effectively, what do you need to have in place? Data readiness 
upstream? API accessibility downstream?

Are there trust issues with letting AI Decisioning run without a human 
in the loop? How do you mitigate that?

For marketers thinking about 2025, what's one closing piece of advice 
you would give them for the year ahead?

A CDP's Best Friend: 
"Shifting Left" Data Quality

Welcome, Greg. Can you start by telling our audience a little about 
MetaRouter and your role there?

You also refer to your platform as a customer data infrastructure. Is that 
a broader concept covering more use cases? Other use cases?

Your marketing team has come up with a catchy phrase calling 
MetaRouter "a CDP's best friend." Why is that?

What's your perspective on the growth of cloud data warehouses and 
lakehouses in marketing? How do you see this changing the martech 
stack?

Data quality is becoming more and more important. How do we make 
sure data is good and trustworthy? How do we govern it?

Any closing advice you'd like to give to marketing and marketing ops 
teams preparing for next year?

Lessons of Composability for 
Marketing Operations
Hi, Sara. Can you tell us about Progress and your role there?

We love the best-of-need! So you'd say that a martech stack is a kind 
of a composable marketing infrastructure?

Are lessons from composability in software development applicable 
to the work of marketers and marketing operation people? Similar 
principles, design patterns?
Right?

How do you see composability applying in the use of new generative 
AI tools such as LLMs?

How do you think that AI will impact the relationship between 
marketing and IT? Are there some things that you believe marketing 
and marketing ops should be able to do themselves?

Any closing advice you'd give to marketers, marketing ops teams as 
they prepare for 2025?

Filling the Gaps in Governance 
for Generative AI

Thank you so much. We would like to start with a spicy topic. Is 
generative AI a bubble? Why and why not?

Are there any use cases for generative AI where you think the 
economics or the ROI will make sense in the short-term versus the 
long-term?

SAS recently produced a report called Marketers and GenAI: Diving 
into the Shallow End, which is kind of a provocative title. Why are we 
in the shallow end and how do we swim beyond it?

So is that how you see generative AI and classic AI intersecting? How 
can they work together?

What would be the closing advice you would want to give to marketers 
and marketing ops teams as they prepare for the year ahead?
